description.en:
While travelling across Japan, Kitahara Minami is pushed off a boat by a beautiful woman he met for the first time. After managing to swim to an island, Minami comes across a bespectacled young man who pronounces, &ldquo;You pass.&rdquo;

The young man, Yuunagi Tenma, is the owner (guard) of  Paradise Isle and since Minami reached the island without dying, he qualifies to be hired. A stunned Minami is told by Yuunagi, &ldquo;From this day forth, you shall be my manservant!&rdquo; 

So he starts working on the island alongside beastfolk, some of whom are part-dog, others part-bird.

One day Minami spies Yuunagi bathing in the sea at night. Yuunagi says it is a ritual to welcome &lsquo;guests&rsquo; (customers). What exactly does Yuunagi mean by 'guest&rsquo;, and what is the purpose of the island? Puzzled by all these mysteries, what will Minami do?!
